description:
Join our growth story!




Are you looking for an exciting new move in your career? SHEIN (www.sheingroup.com) is an international online fashion retailer that’s in an exciting new phase of our continued growth!




If you like to work fast, collaboratively and understand the true value of idea generation with a ‘customer first’ mentality - you’re on your way to being a right fit for us.




As a fast growing business with an immediate need to innovatively build out our talent infrastructure, we’re looking for a dynamic professional who is keen to work in an agile and evolving business environment. There’s work, and then there’s the work you’re passionate about.




The kind of work that’s an extension of who you are. That’s the work we do at SHEIN.




Our values consist of putting the customer first, going all out, acting and adapting, continuous learning & innovating and encouraging synergy & collaboration at all levels within the business.

If you feel like you belong, consider the job description below and apply.

Come shine at SHEIN and join our growth story!




We are currently seeking an experienced Data Analysis Manager(Logistics) to join our team in Germany. As Data Analysis Manager(Logistics) you will be responsible for providing data analysis support for the Head of Fulfillment and other departments. Join us now and be part of a dynamic team, making a significant impact in our organisation's success.




Key Responsibilities:

Provide logistics data and business analysis support for the leadership team (i.e. Dashboard design, Score card design and performance data tracking);
Provide weekly and monthly logistics business reviews, which includes business process optimization indicators, workforce performance indicators, capacity planning recommendations, etc.;
Team engagement and collaboration (i.e. CN performance team, EU logistics operation team and HQ data team, etc.);
Work within time constraints to meet critical business needs.




Skills & Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree and above in data analysis, business analysis or related field;
3+ years of data analysis experiences in E-commerce companies;
Experience with data visualization using Tableau, Quicksight, or similar tools;
Experience working in a fast-paced environment similar to a high-tech start-up; Works well under pressure with the ability to prioritize competing deliverables;
Proficient oral and written communication skills.
